qType.desc:
Type of the field.
Default is U.

values.A: for ASCII; Numeric fields values  contain only standard ASCII characters.
values.I: for INTEGER; Numeric fields values are shown as integer numbers.
values.R: for REAL; Numeric fields values are shown as real numbers.
values.F: for FIX; Numeric fields values are shown as numbers with a fix number of decimals.
values.M: for MONEY; Numeric fields values are shown as in the money format.
values.D: for DATE; Numeric fields values are shown as dates.
values.T: for TIME; Numeric fields values are shown as times.
values.IV: for INTERVAL; Numeric fields values are shown as intervals.

qUseThou.desc:
Defines whether or not a thousands separator must be used.
Default is 0.

qFmt.desc:
Defines the format pattern that applies to qText.
 Is used in connection to the type of the field (parameter qType).
For more information, see Formatting mechanism.
Example: YYYY-MM-DD for a date

qThou.desc:
Defines the thousand separator (if any).
Is used if qUseThou is set to 1.
Example: ,
